“My name is India and I'm the mama of two mostly sweet but always energetic girls, Bee (3) and Thalassa (1). My husband, Damon, grew up in Seattle and his father lived on Vashon when he was little, so the island has always been special and we knew this is where we wanted to raise our family. We moved here two years ago and it's been a wonderful journey. We love spending time together in nature, exploring, appreciating, and protecting her beauty.

I work from home and with the pandemic my work-life balance is nonexistent but work happens in the early morning hours and then I'm with the girls for the remainder of the day. This whole experience through SIP has been hard, fun, special, exhausting, amazing... all kinds of emotions, but I feel lucky that I can call Vashon home. I am looking forward to the day when I can reunite with our community, share a meal, and embrace one another.

I'm a lover of all things that come from the heart and I especially enjoy tea, wine, bread, cut flowers, sweet treats, and anything crafty.“
